edu.unm.health.biocomp.carlsbad

Class carlsbadone_utils

  • Object
    • carlsbadone_utils

  • public class carlsbadone_utils
extends Object
    Static methods for CARLSBAD "one-click" subnet queries. The general use case is to provide interesting subnets based on simple queries. (1) single protein target chosen from a browsable list. (2) single drug compound chosen from a browsable list. By employing CCPs such subnets are uniquely available via CARLSBAD. To do: Any unknowns found? Or are all targets|compounds already associated to the query without CCPs (T-C-T or C-T-C).
    Author:
    Jeremy J Yang

                                                     ArrayList<String> sqls)
                                              throws Exception
        Given a single target, extract CCP-associated network. Comprised of: - active compounds - associated common chemical patterns (CCPs) - CCP-associated compounds
        Parameters:
        dbcon - database connection
        tid_query - query target ID
        fout - XGMML output file
        fout_rgt - XGMML output file, reduced-graph tgts only
        fout_rgtp - XGMML output file, reduced-graph tgts+CCPs
        fout_cpd - output file, compounds, normally SDF
        scaf_min - scaf association threshold [0-1]
        act_filter - activity filter (above avg)
        title - title of subnet
        n_max_a - max number of activities
        n_max_c - max number of compounds
        sqls - return param: SQLs used
        Throws:
        Exception

        public static HashMap<String,Integer> Compound2Network(DBCon dbcon,

                                                       CompoundList cpdlist,
                                                       CCPList ccplist,
                                                       ArrayList<String> sqls)
                                                throws Exception
        Given a single compound, very likely a drug or compound of particular biological interest and for which significant bioactivity data exists, extract CCP-associated network. Comprised of: - targets for which compound is active (knowns) - associated common chemical patterns (CCPs) - CCP-associated compounds - targets for which CCP-associated compounds are active (hypothesis targets) Problem: dangling edges... For Ketoralac, "Edge 24 references unknown node: C102306"
        Parameters:
        dbcon - database connection
        cid_query - query compound ID
        fout - XGMML output file
        fout_rgt - XGMML output file, reduced-graph tgts only
        fout_rgtp - XGMML output file, reduced-graph tgts+CCPs
        fout_cpd - output file, compounds, normally SDF
        scaf_min - scaf association threshold [0-1]
        act_filter - activity filter (above avg)
        title - title of subnet
        n_max_a - max number of activities
        n_max_c - max number of compounds
        sqls - return param: SQLs used
        Throws:
        Exception

        public static HashMap<String,Integer> Disease2Network(DBCon dbcon,
                                                      File fout,

                                                      CCPList ccplist,
                                                      ArrayList<String> sqls)
                                               throws Exception
        Given a single disease (KEGG), extract CCP-associated network. Derived from: - KEGG genes linked to the disease - NCBI_GIs for the KEGG genes - targets in CARLSBAD linked by NCBI_GIs. - active compounds - associated common chemical patterns (CCPs) - CCP-associated compounds
        Parameters:
        dbcon - database connection
        kid_query - query disease KEGG ID
        fout - XGMML output file
        fout_rgt - XGMML output file, reduced-graph tgts only
        fout_rgtp - XGMML output file, reduced-graph tgts+CCPs
        fout_cpd - output file, compounds, normally SDF
        scaf_min - scaf association threshold [0-1]
        act_filter - activity filter (above avg)
        title - title of subnet
        n_max_a - max number of activities
        n_max_c - max number of compounds
        sqls - return param: SQLs used
        Throws:
        Exception
